nd the SKA-low telescopes\nrespectively. We also review the ongoing efforts to develop PTA-relevant\ngeneral relativistic constructs that will be required to search for nanohertz\ngravitational waves from isolated super-massive black hole binary systems like\nblazar OJ 287. These efforts should be relevant to pursue persistent\nmulti-messenger gravitational wave astronomy during the forthcoming era of the\nSKA telescope, the Thirty Meter Telescope, and the next-generation Event\nHorizon Telescope.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 13 Jul 2022 18:24:24 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-12-21"}
