nscintillator materials. The obtained luminous efficiencies were used as input\nof a Monte Carlo simulation to perform a comparative study of the effect of the\nlight-yield non-proportionality on the detection of high-energy electromagnetic\nand hadronic showers. The result of this study indicates that, if the\ncalorimeter response is calibrated by using the energy deposit of minimum\nionizing particles, the measured shower energy might be affected by a\nsignificant systematic shift, at the level of few percent, whose sign and\nmagnitude depend specifically on the type of scintillator material used.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 14 Jul 2022 06:58:55 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-09-22"}
